{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05354/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05354"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:53:54"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman speaks to a man wearing a blank expression."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05354","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05354"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1/9c731fd7-abc0-4abf-a40a-4c55e49bd2c7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:39:10.060Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>According to lighting cameraman Mike Bauman, PTA provided the production team with Mary Blume’s <em>The Master of Us All: Balenciaga, His Workrooms, His World</em> as a reference point (Lux Lighting, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW84429253 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kpi393XkzUo\"><u>Lighting Phantom Thread</u></a>”).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:33.708326199650855,37.41684773790354,275.6249999999999,225.60897435897442"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1/87554251-4115-4631-bcea-9a82548a7506","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:39:29.942Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds has spent much of the event avoiding looking directly at it, such as <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW201612001 BCX0\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-05207.html\"><u>when he hid his head during the press conference</u></a>. During this conversation, he avoids Alma’s probing gaze, staring at the ground as she tries to convince him his work is too good for Barbara. Although he clearly agrees with her, he initially attempts to ignore those feelings, to not face the situation head on. The moment he finally meets Alma’s gaze is when he decides to take the dress back from Barabara. When he meets her eyes, he decides to take her comments seriously, and trust her judgement. It is a rare moment where he allows her to take some control and treats her as an equal.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05354/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1313.7564031227275,484.6203733789293,440.98557692307713,169.11858974358967"}}}]}]}]}